  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting environmental human rights defenders in Peru networking and multi-level advocacy</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will support environmental human rights defenders and their communities and organisations afected by extractive projects in Cusco, Apur&#xED;mac, Puno, Cajamarca, Aqeuipa, Pasco, Amazon&#xED;a and others. Red Muqui and 10 other NGOs members of the coalition working on social impacts of mining as well as other Human Rights organisations have started a National Campaign for Environmental defenders since 2021, and this project will support defenders who are facing criminalisation, stigmatisation, attacks and threats for protecting our common home and human rights in the face of extractive and other megaprojects. This will be done via trainings, exchanges and networking to develop recomendations and public and communication campaigns and advocacy activities to improve their protection and support, also focusing on the need to ratify the Escaz&#xFA; Agreement in Peru.</narrative>
  </description>
